          <h1>Skeptia: Youth &amp; AI</h1>
          <p class="lead">
            Helping young people use AI with judgment, curiosity, and critical thought.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <div class="container cards-grid two">
          <article class="card">
            <p class="card-kicker">What it is</p>
            <h2>A youth-focused initiative for thoughtful AI use.</h2>
            <p>
              Skeptia explores how young people can grow up with AI in ways that are practical, reflective, and grounded.
            </p>
            <p>
              The goal is not to position youth against AI, but to help them use it without weakening judgment, critical thinking, or confidence in their own reasoning.
            </p>
          </article>

          <article class="card">
            <p class="card-kicker">Why it matters</p>
            <h2>AI is unavoidable. Passive dependence should not be.</h2>
            <p>
              AI tools are already part of everyday life across education, communication, creativity, and research. That makes thoughtful use increasingly important.
            </p>
            <p>
              Skeptia focuses on helping youth recognize risks such as overreliance, misinformation, shallow understanding, and uncritical acceptance of confident outputs.
            </p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <div class="container cards-grid two">
          <article class="card">
            <p class="card-kicker">How it works</p>
            <h2>Workshops, scenarios, and critical inquiry.</h2>
            <ul class="feature-list">
              <li>Recognizing when AI is helping versus replacing thinking</li>
              <li>Tracing claims back to sources and checking reliability</li>
              <li>Identifying hallucinations, bias, and weak evidence</li>
              <li>Using structured questions to evaluate AI-generated content</li>
              <li>Maintaining independent judgment in real situations</li>
            </ul>
          </article>

          <article class="card">
            <p class="card-kicker">Workshop direction</p>
            <h2>Symbiosis, not rejection.</h2>
            <p>
              Skeptia is built around the idea that youth should learn how to work with AI well, not simply avoid it.
            </p>
            <p>
              The emphasis is on practical strategies that strengthen human agency: pausing before trusting, checking before repeating, and thinking before delegating.
            </p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <div class="container split-feature">
          <div>
            <p class="section-kicker">Core principle</p>
            <h2>Use AI as a tool, not as a substitute for thought.</h2>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p>
              Skeptia treats AI as something to work with deliberately. That means preserving curiosity, judgment, and a healthy habit of verification even as AI becomes more embedded in everyday life.
            </p>
            <p>
              Over time, this project can grow into workshops, public resources, and educational frameworks that help young people stay grounded in the middle of rapid technological change.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
